---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import LifeCanvas from "../../components/life/LifeCanvas.tsx";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Game of Life"
  description="Conway's Game of Life reimagined as soft-body metaballs — cells spring to life, melt away, and drift through a rainbow as they age."
>
  <article class="document document--wide">
    <p class="label" data-animate>
      <a href="/fun" class="back">← Fun stuff</a>
    </p>
    <h1 data-animate>Conway's Game of Life</h1>
    <hr class="rule" data-animate />

    <p data-animate>
      Conway's Game of Life is a cellular automaton: a grid of cells lives or
      dies each generation by a few tiny rules, and from that simplicity comes
      surprisingly lifelike behavior. This is my take on it — instead of crisp
      squares, living cells are rendered as soft-body metaballs that spring into
      existence, melt away when they die, and glow through a neon spectrum as
      they age, merging into living plasma. It uses the same gooey metaball
      technique as the fluid blobs behind the rest of the site, turned up to
      neon.
    </p>

    <div data-animate>
      <LifeCanvas client:visible />
    </div>

    <p class="muted hint" data-animate>
      Click or drag on the grid to paint cells. The rules: a living cell with
      two or three neighbors survives; a dead cell with exactly three neighbors
      is born; everything else dies.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style is:global>
  .life {
    margin: var(--space-4) 0;
  }
  .life-stage {
    width: 100%;
    height: min(60vh, 520px);
    border: 1px solid #2a2550;
    border-radius: 10px;
    /* Deep indigo backdrop so the neon metaballs read as glowing plasma. */
    background: radial-gradient(120% 120% at 50% 25%, #16123a 0%, #08071a 70%);
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: inset 0 0 60px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.55);
  }
  .life-stage canvas {
    display: block;
    /* The blur+contrast pass thresholds the soft circles into merged, gooey
       metaball silhouettes; saturate + brightness push the neon glow. */
    filter: blur(7px) contrast(9) saturate(1.25) brightness(1.12);
    touch-action: none;
    cursor: crosshair;
  }

  .life-controls {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-2);
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
  }
  .life-controls button {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-sm);
    color: var(--ink);
    background: var(--bg-raised);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-3);
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: color 0.18s ease, border-color 0.18s ease, transform 0.18s ease;
  }
  .life-controls button:hover:not(:disabled) {
    color: var(--accent);
    border-color: var(--accent);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }
  .life-controls button:disabled {
    opacity: 0.45;
    cursor: not-allowed;
  }
  .life-controls .speed {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.6ch;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-xs);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
  }
  .life-controls .speed input {
    accent-color: var(--accent);
  }
  .life-note {
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
    font-size: var(--fs-sm);
    color: var(--ink-muted);
  }
</style>

<style>
  .back {
    border-bottom: none;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
  }
  .back:hover {
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .hint {
    font-size: var(--fs-sm);
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
  }
</style>
